(2867, 1, '2017-11-17 14:49:55', '2017-11-17 09:04:55', '<h1>Nepal lose to Afghanistan by 7 wickets</h1>\n<a href=\"http://www.pmstnepal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/19.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-2517\" src=\"http://www.pmstnepal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/19-300x184.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"184\" /></a>\n\nNov 17, 2017- \'Afghanistan Under-19 beat Nepal Under-19 \' by seven wickets in the second semi-finals being played at the Kinrara Oval in Kuala Lumpur on Friday to reach the finals of the ACC U-19 Asia Cup.\n\nThe Afghan U-19 team will play the finals against Pakistan U-19, who defeated Bangladesh by 2 runs via Duckworth–Lewis method as rain stopped the play on Thursday..\n\nLosing the toss to Afghanistan, Nepal U-19 was called to bat first and had posted a meager total of 103 after being all out in 28 overs.\n\nDespite heavy rain stopping the play after the 18th over, the Afghani team reached the target in 20.3 overs losing just three wickets.\n\nOpener Rahmanullah Gurbaz made it look too easy for the Afghans as he 71 scored runs off 65 deliveries before being caught by Shahab Alam off Sandeep Lamichhane’s delivery in 19.1 overs. Ikram Ali Khil supported Gurbaz and scored 18 runs.\n\nNepali bowlers came back strong but too late as Pawan Sarraf and Lamichhane took two wickets in two overs after the match resumed following the rains. Sarraf claimed the wicket of Ikram in 18.2 overs.\n\nSarraf, Lamichhane and Kamal Singh Airee took one wicket each for Nepal. Afghan opener Ibrahim Zadran was caught behind down the leg side in 5.1 overs by Aasif Sheikh off Airee’s delivery.\n\nEarlier, Nepal showcased a poor batting performance against their rival with openers failing to stay in the crease for long.\n\nHowever, Anil Kumar Sah came out to the rescue and scored 50 runs off 57 balls before being bowled by Mujeeb Ur Rahman in 23.2 overs. Other Nepali batsmen could not score in double figures.\n\nFor Afghanistan, Mujeeb was the star bowler taking 6 Nepali wickets for just 28 runs in his 10 over spell with an economy of 2.8. Likewise, Qais Ahmad took 2 wickets in his six over spell.', 'ACC U-19 Asia Cup: Nepal lose to Afghanistan by 7 wickets', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'acc-u-19-asia-cup-nepal-lose-afghanistan-7-wickets', '', '', '2017-11-17 14:49:55', '2017-11-17 09:04:55', '', 0, 'http://www.pmstnepal.com/?post_type=gallery&amp;p=2516', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2868, 1, '2017-11-19 15:11:08', '2017-11-19 09:26:08', '<h1>Interview with an Make-up Artist : Seema Gurung</h1>\n<a href=\"http://www.pmstnepal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/sem.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-2519\" src=\"http://www.pmstnepal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/sem-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\nSeema Gurung - Born in Jhapa (Kerkha) and raised in Kathmandu , Seema Gurung was selected in numerous recording artists, music vedios, events, editorials and ad campaigns. Seema is known for her ultra-hygienic approach, understanding of beauty, trends and passion for symmetry which appeals to the likes of many artists.\n\nWhere do you get your inspiration from?\nI get my inspiration from so many different things: fashion, travel, history, different cultures, plants and nature.\n\nWho are some people that have inspired you throughout your carrer ?\nI was always looking up to supermodels. Strong images of powerful women. They were,  like,  my superheroes.\n\nHOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN A MAKEUP ARTIST AND HOW DID YOU GET YOUR START IN THE INDUSTRY?\n5 years,  I started in Korea and trained at Academy and knee deep in fashion editorials working every job I was offered for free. It was very hard at first to find job.\n\nWHAT DO YOU LOVE MOST ABOUT MAKE UP?\nMaking someone look so different. Changing people’s image to suit their mood or moment. It’s endless.  The never ending boundless beauty and glamour.\n\nIF YOU WEREN’T A MAKEUP ARTIST, WHAT ELSE WOULD YOU DO?\nI don’t know how to answer this as I have never taken my mind off being a makeup artist.  My focus has been a constant for most of my life.  This is what I was born to do. But I was also fond of being a pilot and take a tour around the world.\n\nHOW WOULD YOU DESCRIBE YOUR SIGNATURE LOOK AND WHAT IS IT ABOUT YOUR STYLE THAT SETS YOU APART FROM OTHER MAKEUP ARTISTS?\nI like to make a face pop on the red carpet. I like to look healthy and I rarely send anyone out of my chair without careful and light,  appropriate contouring. I like to dress as barbie doll with curly hair and a good eye art.\n\nWHAT IS THE MOST IMPORTANT BEAUTY ADVICE THAT YOU CAN GIVE TO WOMEN?\nInvest in your mind, body and soul. Shoes come and go, but your skin needs more than a yearly check-up. Invest in a good regular facial and nurture yourself with massages and quiet rest from time to time.\n\nWHAT ARE SOME COMMON BEAUTY MISTAKES THAT WOMEN MAKE?\nI often see great dabs of shimmery bronzer . It looks great on shoots and in very specific areas but some people circle it all over and you end up looking like an orange ball. Not good! Less is more. I also see people finding hard controlling on make up and colour combination should be used systematically so it gives natural and perfect look.\n\nWHAT PRODUCTS DO YOU THINK SHOULD BE A STAPLE IN EVERY WOMAN\'S PURSE?\nMAKE UP FOR EVER Aqua Shadow. In one swipe and a quick smudge you can have a soft durable smoky eye in 2 minutes. Follow with your fave mascara.\nNaturally! Because you never know when plans change and these two items are small enough to take anywhere.\n\nWHAT’S YOUR FAVORITE MAKEUP BRUSH?\nMy fave makeup brush is actually an eyebrow brush. It’s a giant soft version of the tiny hard angled ones you usually see and it works great creating a full, luscious natural looking brow in one swipe.\n\nWHAT’S YOUR FAVORITE MAKE UP FOR EVER PRODUCT?\nMAC , NAKED and CRAYON. Covers every color spectrum I have ever needed to use in my kit.\n\nWhat trait do you most admire in a man or a woman?\nBeautiful eyes. Any time I see beautiful eyes, they’re always, like, blue.\n\nWhat is your worst nightmare?\nI used to have the craziest fear of losing teeth. I would have nightmares about that all the time. But it’s the craziest thing, because I feel like that’s one of the easiest things to fix. You just get veneers or something. Haha...(laughs)\n\nHow do you feel about your career achievements?\nI feel very happy as my dream of beind makeup artist changed into reality. I am also glad that I chose this path and I can make someone look different,beautiful\nand charming.\n\nDo you still have, \"I can\'t believe this is my life,\" moments?\nAll the time.When I find the chance to art eye and give my best shot make up.\n\nDo you have a secret talent?\nI am a balck belt of Shitoryu Karate.\n\nWho was your first crush?\nMy first crush was this kid at 7 class who told me he loved make up artist. He was so charming and handsome.\n\nWhat keeps you grounded?\nMy friends and my family because they just make fun of me all day. That\'s the best. When they come over while I\'m\ngetting they\'ll just be teasing me.\' I love them.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Interview with an Make-up Artist : Seema Gurung', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'interview-make-artist-seema-gurung', '', '', '2017-11-19 15:11:08', '2017-11-19 09:26:08', '', 0, 'http://www.pmstnepal.com/?post_type=gallery&amp;p=2518', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2869, 1, '2017-11-19 16:14:11', '2017-11-19 10:29:11', '<h1>प्रकाशको निधनमा भारतीय विदेश मन्त्रीदेखि पूर्व राजाका प्रमुख सचिवसम्मले दिए श्रद्धान्जली</h1>\n<a href=\"http://www.pmstnepal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/prakash-dahal.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-2524\" src=\"http://www.pmstnepal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/prakash-dahal-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\nकाठमाडौं, मंसिर ३ – माओवादी अध्यक्ष तथा पूर्व प्रधानमन्त्री पुष्पकमल दाहाल प्रचण्डका छोरा तथा माओवादीका पोलिटब्यूरो सदस्य प्रकाश दाहालको आइतबार विहान हृदयघातबाट निधन भएको छ ।\n\nप्रकाशको असामयिक निधनपछि चुनावी कार्यक्रममा झापामा रहनुभएका प्रचण्ड बिहानै काठमाडौं फर्कनुभएको छ । त्यस्तै चुनावी कार्यक्रममा जिल्लामा रहेका विभिन्न दलका नेताहरु पनि काठमाडौं चुनावी कार्यक्रम स्थगित गरेर काठमाडौं फर्केका छन् । नयाँ शक्ति नेपालका संयोजक डाक्टर बाबुराम भट्टराई पनि गोरखामा आफ्नो चुनावी कार्यक्रम स्थगन गरेर काठमाडौं फर्कनु भएको छ ।\n\nपछिल्लो समय प्रकाश दाहालले प्रचण्डको स्वकीय सचिव मात्रै भएर होइन, प्रचण्ड तथा पार्टीका चुनावी कार्यक्रमहरुको सामाजिक सञ्जालमा अपडेट गराउने लगायत सञ्चारमाध्यमलाई जानकारी गराउने कार्य गर्नुहुन्थ्यो ।\n\nप्रकाशको निधनमा राष्ट्रपति विद्यादेवी भण्डारी प्रचण्ड निवास लाजिम्पाट पुगेरै दाहाल परिवारलाई समवेदना दिनुभएको छ । उपराष्ट्रपति नन्दवहादुर पुन माओवादी पार्टी कार्यालय पेरिसडाँडामा पुगेर समवेदना दिनुभएको छ ।त्यस्तै प्रधानमन्त्री शेरबहादर देउवाले सामाजिक सञ्जालमार्फत समवेदना प्रकट गर्नुभएको छ ।\n\nत्यस्तै पूर्वप्रधानमन्त्रीहरु झलनाथ खनाल तथा माधवकुमार नेपाल माओवादी केन्द्रको पार्टी कार्यालय पुगेरै प्रकाशको पार्थिव शरीरमा श्रद्धाञ्जली व्यक्त गर्नुभएको छ ।\n\nत्यस्तै चुनावी कार्यक्रममै झापामा रहनुभएका नेकपा एमालेका अध्यक्ष तथा पूर्व प्रधानमन्त्री केपी शर्मा ओलीले काठमाडौं फर्कनुअघि प्रचण्डलाई झापामै भेट्नुभएको थियो । क्रान्तिकारी माओवादीका अध्यक्ष मोहन वैद्य किरणले पनि पार्टी कार्यालयमै पुगेर श्रद्धान्जली व्यक्त गर्नुभएको छ । त्यस्तै पूर्व राजा ज्ञानेन्द्रका सचिव पशुपतिभक्त महर्जनले पनि श्रद्धान्जली व्यक्त गर्नुभएको छ ।\n\nत्यस्तै प्रकाशको पार्थीव शरीरमा श्रद्धाञ्जली व्यक्त गर्न माओवादीका नेता कार्यकर्ता तथा विभिन्न दलका नेता कार्यकर्ताको उपस्थिति रहेको थियो ।\n\nत्यस्तै पूर्वप्रधानमन्त्री प्रचण्ड पुत्र प्रकाशको निधनमा भारतीय विदेशमन्त्री सुश्मा स्वराजले ट्वीटरमार्फत दाहाल परीवारलाई समवेदना प्रकट गर्नुभएको छ ।\n\nत्यस्तै राप्रपाका अध्यक्ष कमल थापालेखि विवेकशील साझा पार्टीका संयोजक रवीन्द्र मिश्रसम्मले सामाजिक सञ्जालमा स्वर्गीय प्रकाश दाहालप्रति श्रद्धाञ्जली व्यक्त गर्नुको साथै शोकसन्तप्त दाहाल परिवारप्रति समवेदना प्रकट गरेका छन् ।\n\n&nbsp;', 'प्रकाशको निधनमा भारतीय विदेश मन्त्रीदेखि पूर्व राजाका प्रमुख सचिवसम्मले दिए श्रद्धान्जली', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '%e0%a4%aa%e0%a5%8d%e0%a4%b0%e0%a4%95%e0%a4%be%e0%a4%b6%e0%a4%95%e0%a5%8b-%e0%a4%a8%e0%a4%bf%e0%a4%a7%e0%a4%a8%e0%a4%ae%e0%a4%be-%e0%a4%ad%e0%a4%be%e0%a4%b0%e0%a4%a4%e0%a5%80%e0%a4%af-%e0%a4%b5', '', '', '2017-11-19 16:14:11', '2017-11-19 10:29:11', '', 0, 'http://www.pmstnepal.com/?post_type=gallery&amp;p=2523', 0, 'post', '', 0),
