(3050, 1, '2018-07-01 15:38:46', '2018-07-01 09:53:46', 'A feature film to be directed by Binod Paudel, who is the principal of Oscar College of Film Studies, was announced on Monday amid a function held in the Capital. The film will feature Swastima Khadka, noted actress of films such as Hostel and Chhakka Panja 2, as a tempo driver.\r\n<div class=\"kan_ads nic-asia-wrap clearfix\">\r\n<div class=\"nic-asia-wrap-ad-the-kathmandu-post\">The film, according to director Paudel, will explore the character of a tempo driver. “Our aim is to portray a familiar lifestyle, that of a tempo driver, as realistically as we can,” Paudel said speaking at the event. Paudel is the scriptwriter of Saanghuro, which told the story of a family residing in one of Kathmandu’s slums.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n“I find it rather ironic that one should talk about the film in an announcement ceremony. A film should speak for itself,” Paudel said, adding, “With the film, we have tried to portray the reality of a certain class living in Nepal’s urban area. If nothing else, you’ll find sincerity in the work we do.” Speaking at the event, actress Swastima Khadka said that the film will be special to her, for the film “is not about glamour but about exploring the character.” Preparing for the character, Khadka is currently undergoing trainings.\r\n\r\nAlongside Khadka, the film will also feature actors Joyes Pandey, Mukun Bhusal, Laxmi Bardewa, Dipak Chhetri and Ujwal Adhikari.', 'Swastima Khadka  to play tempo driver', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3048-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-01 15:38:46', '2018-07-01 09:53:46', '', 3048, 'http://www.pmstnepal.com/uncategorized/3048-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3051, 1, '2018-07-01 15:53:08', '2018-07-01 10:08:08', 'After debuting in 2012’s runaway blockbuster Loot, Saugat Malla remained, in the ensuing years, the most sought-after actor in the Nepali film industry. Malla, who started as a theatre actor, made that rare transition to the big screen, picking up one project after another.\r\n<div class=\"kan_ads nic-asia-wrap clearfix\">\r\n<div class=\"nic-asia-wrap-ad-the-kathmandu-post\">But, despite him giving fine performances in several films he has appeared in, only a few have gone on to become successes, critically, which has prompted critics to wonder whether Malla has wasted his talent picking up one feeble project after another.</div>\r\n</div>\r\nMalla is now set to make his comeback in the same gangstar avatar as in his debut film, with the Mukunda Bhatta-directorial Gang of Gani.\r\n\r\nGang of Gani, a drama, is Malla’s second teamup with Bhatta after 2017’s Lappan Chhappan.\r\n\r\nAccording to director Bhatta, Gang of Gani will be shot in locations around Darchula and Kathmandu.\r\n\r\nThe film is yet to be announced and, besides Malla, the actors to play in the film are yet to be finalised.', 'Saugat to essay a gangster in Gang of Gani', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'saugat-to-essay-a-gangster-in-gang-of-gani', '', '', '2018-07-01 15:53:08', '2018-07-01 10:08:08', '', 0, 'http://www.pmstnepal.com/?p=3051', 0, 'post', '', 0),
