(3081, 1, '2018-07-12 18:05:23', '2018-07-12 12:20:23', 'Writer and tele-serial director Sangita Shrestha has now come up with a feature film, Katha Kathmandu.\r\n<div class=\"kan_ads nic-asia-wrap clearfix\">\r\n<div class=\"nic-asia-wrap-ad-the-kathmandu-post\">Shrestha is the director of the series Katha Premka, which used to air on Kantipur Television and author of an anthology of short stories, Kathama Aljhiyeko Prem.</div>\r\n</div>\r\nThe film features actors Priyanka Karki, Aayushman DS Joshi, Sanjog Koirala, Sandhya KC, Prekshya Adhikari, and Pramod Agrahari, and presents the stories of, as the poster of the film promises, lust, love and life. The film also features a cameo role by singer Indira Joshi.\r\n<div class=\"row tkp_ad tkp_detail_bwtn_content_rectangle\"></div>\r\nAccording to producers, Aahana Films, the film portrays the separate stories of separate characters residing in Kathmandu.\r\n\r\n“The seeds of Katha Kathmandu were sown very early on when I was directing the tele-serial. The series not only garnered good responses but also offered to direct a feature. I was not yet prepared to do a feature then. Instead, I wrote a short collection, the response from which further buoyed me as a storyteller,” director Shrestha said. “In the upcoming feature, I have tried to tell an all-too-familiar story but with a different approach.”\r\n\r\nKatha Kathmandu will hit theatres around the nation on Sept 28.', 'Katha Kathmandu: ‘Stories of love, lust and life’', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3079-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-12 18:05:23', '2018-07-12 12:20:23', '', 3079, 'http://www.pmstnepal.com/uncategorized/3079-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
