(3195, 1, '2018-08-12 18:18:44', '2018-08-12 12:33:44', 'Subsequent to winning praises for the brining the uncommon story of Hari to life and breaking the typecast for the \'Nepali hero\' in the process, Bipin Karki is good to go to convey yet another non-conventional character to screen with his new component film Prasad. The upcoming film, which wrapped up its main photography this week and stars Namrataa Shrestha and Nischal Basnet close by Karki, will be up for release in December.\r\n\r\nTalking about his new pursuit, Karki, whose technique acting of particular characters has made him a commonly recognized name, stated, \"At the heart of Prasad is inter-caste marriage in which I have portrayed the role of the husband belonging to a lower caste. My approach while depicting this part, as in my past film, is the same: I have attempted to give the character some genuine resonances so the crowd can relate and understand him. In any project, be it before or now, my approach continues as before, which many have said conflicts with the grain of what a \'saint\' in a Nepali film ought to be.\"\r\n\r\nKarki, in any case, recognizes that conveying new stories to screen does not ensure film industry achievement. \"In my last task, Hari, I played a man pondering a personality emergency, and the film was test,\" Karki stated, \"However the film didn\'t charge well in the cinema world on the grounds that possibly it required the ‘traditional’ Nepali filmgoers to alter their tastes. Our industry is advancing and all the better we can do is keep on pushing the story assist until the point when a tipping point is ideally come to.\"\r\n\r\nThe film will also see director Nischal Basnet make a comeback as an actor. “I felt like I really ‘acted’ this time. Maybe it’s because of my own maturity as an actor, but more than that, it’s because of the director,” Basnet said. He also mentioned that because the story delves into psychological conflicts between its characters, the shooting 